. Kailas R. Jadhav Designation: IQAC Coordinator Qualification: M.Sc(Computer Management), Ph.D. --> Mobile: 9423522278 Email: joykailas@gmail.com Internal Quality Assurance Cell (IQAC) (A NAAC Initiative for Sustained Academic Excellence) Introduction The Internal Quality Assurance Cell (IQAC) serves as the cornerstone of our college’s commitment to continual improvement and academic excellence. Established in accordance with the National Assessment and Accreditation Council (NAAC) guidelines, the IQAC is a proactive mechanism to build and ensure a quality culture within the institution. It functions as a dynamic system for planning, guiding, and monitoring quality assurance and enhancement activities across all dimensions of academic and administrative operations. More than a compliance body, the IQAC is a catalyst for change—encouraging innovation, fostering inclusivity, and strengthening accountability. Objectives To develop a system for conscious, consistent, and catalytic improvement in the academic and administrative performance of the institution. To promote measures for institutional functioning towards quality enhancement through internalization of quality culture and institutionalization of best practices. Strategies ❖Ensuring timely, efficient, and progressive performance of academic, administrative, and financial tasks. ❖ Optimizing and integrating modern methods of teaching, learning, and evaluation. ❖ Enhancing the credibility of evaluation procedures. ❖ Facilitating the creation of a learner-centric environment conducive to quality education. ❖ Promoting research, innovation, and consultancy activities. ❖ Collaborating with stakeholders to enhance curriculum relevance and employability. ❖ Institutionalizing best practices and benchmarking against global standards. Functions ❖ Development and application of quality benchmarks for various academic and administrative activities. ❖ Facilitating a student-centric teaching-learning environment through feedback collection and analysis. ❖ Organizing workshops, seminars, and faculty development programs on quality-related themes. ❖ Documentation and dissemination of best practices and quality enhancement initiatives. ❖ Preparation and submission of the Annual Quality Assurance Report (AQAR) to NAAC. ❖ Acting as a nodal agency for coordinating quality-related activities including adoption and dissemination of good practices. ❖ Maintaining an institutional database through MIS for the purpose of maintaining/enhancing institutional quality. Benefits ❖ Provides a structured and consistent approach for quality assurance and enhancement. ❖ Bridges the gap between academic planning and institutional execution. ❖ Ensures stakeholder satisfaction through continuous assessment and improvements. ❖ Encourages the development of an organized methodology for decision-making and performance tracking. ❖ Promotes a quality-driven institutional ethos leading to enhanced national and international reputation. Copyright © 2026 Go to Old Website... --> Contacts Ambajogai Road, Latur - 413531 (Maharashtra) India. Contact No.: +91 9420213625, 8329449098, 9028603980 --> Email: cocsit365@rediffmail.com Custom Search COCSIT OFFICIAL Scan to get instant help... WhatsApp QR Code Back to Top